title: Voice of the Beehive - Bee-Sides, interview, history
description:
Voice of the Beehive - Bee-Sides, cover art, interview, history

If you don't know Voice of the Beehive, you're really missing out.  I usually describe them as similar to the Go-Go's with more clever lyrics.  Fronted by two sisters, Tracey Bryn and Missy Belland, with Tracey doing the bulk of the songwriting.  Lots of fun songs from a fantastic band who just never got the breaks to hit it really big.  I also included an 55-minute interview from 2008 I found on Revenge of the 80s Radio that includes several songs.  Also, their website appears to have died, so I included a long .txt file I had copied-and-pasted detailing their history.

From Discogs dot com:  The band made this CD of demos available from their website in 2003.  Two of the 12 tracks were previously released in the same form as B-sides (Shine Away & Pocket Sized). The rest were previously unheard demo takes or new demos.
